The course aims to provide an overview of related approaches to social planning (strategic planning, planning approaches, socio-economics). It considers planning in the specific economic and socio-political context. It handles various areas of social planning and related fields and different levels of social planning. It looks at the different stages of social planning: pre-evaluation, involvement and decision-making, implementation, re-evaluation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) main concepts of planning and social issues/areas; 2) basic steps of strategic planning; 3) social planning as a service and policy planning; process 4) planning at different levels: country, county, local municipality.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) has knowledge of strategic planning cycle and different stages; 2) has knowledge of main approaches to social planning; 3) has knowledge of economic and political context in planning; 4) has knowledge of different levels and scope of social planning; 5) has knowlege of ethics and the legal context of social planning; 6) has knowledge and skills of planning socio-economic well-being for the local government level.
